0target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20assessment%20of%20Ukrainian%20tactics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20by%20analyst%20Nataliya%20Bugayova.%20She%20argued%20that%20the%20West%20needed%20to%20show%20more%20faith%20in%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Ukrainian%20forces%20have%20done%20what%20successful%20militaries%20do%20%E2%80%94%20they%20have%20adapted%20and%20are%20now%20advancing.%20Ukraine%20recognized%20the%20realities%20of%20Russian%20defenses%20much%20faster%20than%20Western%20policymakers%2C%20who%20were%20expecting%20a%20rapid%20Ukrainian%20breakthrough%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bugayova.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20argument%20echoes%20that%20of%20a%20US%20veteran%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-shouldnt-follow-us-military-doctrine-warfare-better-trainer-russia-2023-9%5C%22%3Espoke%20to%20Insider's%20Sin%C3%A9ad%20Baker%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20training%20Ukrainian%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20use%20American%20doctrine%20here%2C%20we%20would%20definitely%20have%20a%20bad%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20trainer%2C%20who%20uses%20the%20callsign%20Jackie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20the%20summer%20Ukraine%20launched%20a%20counteroffensive%20to%20breach%20Russia's%20formidable%20defenses%20in%20eastern%20and%20southern%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20forces%20uses%20tactics%20learned%20over%20months%20in%20the%20training%20camps%20of%20NATO%20armies.%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%20at%20the%20time%20that%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwestern-trained-ukrainian-troops-are-abandoning-us-tactics-report-2023-8%5C%22%3Einvolved%20attacking%20Russian%20positions%20in%20large%20groups%20using%20complicated%20maneuvers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20suffering%20heavy%20casualties%20Ukraine%20abandoned%20that%20approach.%20Instead%20it%20fell%20back%20on%20more%20familiar%20tactics%20involving%20smaller%20groups%20backed%20by%20pr