ons%20make%20it%20extremely%20costly%20and%20complicated%20for%20a%20provider%20to%20open%20up%20or%20expand%20a%20facility.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20housing%20affordability%20crisis%20is%20making%20all%20of%20this%20worse%2C%C2%A0as%20the%20cost%20of%20rent%20means%20it's%20increasingly%C2%A0difficult%20for%20providers%2C%C2%A0especially%20those%20who%20provide%20childcare%20in%20their%20homes%2C%20to%20afford%20their%20spaces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChildcare%20facilities%20often%20aren't%20allowed%20in%20residential%20areas%2C%20where%20kids%20live%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChildcare%20providers%20that%20operate%20out%20of%20residences%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20home-based%20childcare%20%E2%80%94%20often%20have%20the%20most%20trouble%20with%20these%20regulations.%20Many%20cities%20and%20towns%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Flocal%2Flanow%2Fla-me-illegal-businesses-20180919-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20it%20illegal%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20businesses%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statesman.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Flocal%2F2013%2F02%2F13%2Fstatesman-watch-city-cracks-down-on-business-operating-in-brentwood-neighborhood%2F9877009007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopen%20up%20in%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20the%20majority%20of%20zoned%20land%20in%20US%20cities%20is%20exclusively%20for%20single-family%20homes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20laws%20that%20were%20supposedly%20designed%20to%20protect%20children%20by%20keeping%20businesses%20like%20childcare%20centers%20out%20of%20quiet%20residential%20neighborhoods%20are%20now%20hurting%20them%2C%20experts%20say.%20Historically%2C%20separating%20residential%20neighborhoods%20from%20businesses%20and%20industrial%20sites%20was%20justified%20as%20%26quot%3Bproviding%20a%20safe%20and%20quiet%20environment%20for%20the%20rearing%20of%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Charles%20Gardner%2C%20a%20housing%20researcher%20at%20the%20Mercatus%20Center%20at%20George%20Mason%20University.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBearing%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20it%20would%20seem%20on%20its%20surface%20odd%20that%20zoning%20codes%20would%20prohibit%20childcare%20facilities%20from%20opening%20in%20residential%20zones%20and%20require%20that%20they%20operate%20in%20commercial%20districts%20where%20there%20may%20be%20more%20noise%2C%20more%20commotion%2C%20more%20traffic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20home-based%20operations%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbipartisanpolicy.org%2Fblog%2Fnationwide-survey-child-care-in-the-time-of-coronavirus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20a%20key%20service%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20often%20satisfy%20linguistic%20and%20cultural%20needs%20families%20have%2C%20can%20operate%20in%20places%20without%20easy%20access%20to%20business%20districts%2C%20and%20providers%20can%20care%20for%20their%20own%20young%20kids%20while%20also%20doing%20their%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20and%20cities%20are%20starting%20to%20eliminate%20some%20of%20the%20barriers%20to%20opening%20up%20or%20expanding%20a%20facility%2C%20particularly%20those%20in%20peoples'%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20California%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.childcarelaw.org%2Fcontent%2Ffrequently-asked-questions-sb-234-the-keeping-kids-close-to-home-act%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassed%20a%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20prohibits%20any%20city%20or%20county%20government%20from%20requiring%20home-based%20childcare%20providers%20to%20get%20a%20zoning%20permit%20or%20business%20license.%20This%20allows%20childcare%20centers%20to%20operate%20out%20of%20all%20types%20of%20homes%20and%20avoid%20getting%20community%20approval%2C%20which%20disproportionately%20empowers%20homeowners%20and%20older%2C%20wealthier%20folks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20implementing%20the%20law%20is%20proving%20difficult.%20Many%20cities%20just%20aren't%20complying%20%E2%80%94%20often%20because%20they%20don't%20know%20about%20the%20state%20law.%20And%20affected%20providers%20don't%20always%20know%20their%20rights.%20Laurie%20Furstenfeld%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20Berkeley%2C%20California-based%20Child%20Care%20Law%20Center%2C%20is%20working%20with%20cities%20to%20get%20them%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20law.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20doing%20Public%20Record%20Act%20requests%20lately%20for%20a%20few%20cities%20just%20to%20see%20if%20they%20are%20charging%20them%20and%20unfortunately%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20have%20been%2C%20even%20when%20they%20say%20that%20they're%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Furstenfeld%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELandlords%20often%20discriminate%20against%20renters%20wanting%20to%20open%20a%20childcare%20center%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20insidious%20problem%20is%20landlord%20discrimination%20against%20childcare%20providers.%20Furstenfeld's%20organization%20is%20working%20to%20sue%20property%20owners%20for%20evicting%20or%20refusing%20to%20rent%20to%20providers%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20prove.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20pretty%20bright%20line%20rule%20with%20the%20zoning%20and%20business%20licenses.%20It's%20a%20bit%20harder%20to%20get%20to%20the%20heart%20of%20when%20somebody%20denies%20somebody%20to%20rent%2C%26quot%3B%20Furstenfeld%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20are%20also%20addressing%20issues%20impacting%20childcare%20in%20residences.%20Oregon%2C%20Oklahoma%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20and%20Montana%20have%20all%20passed%20legislation%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20home-based%20providers%20to%20operate.%20The%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20city%20council%20recently%20passed%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20ban%20discrimination%20against%20home-based%20childcare%20providers%20by%20condo%20associations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20without%20many%20of%20these%20burdensome%20land-use%20regulations%2C%20childcare%20will%20likely%20still%20be%20exorbitantly%20expensive%20for%20too%20many%20parents%20and%20bad%20business%20for%20providers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20our%20ideal%20world%2C%20it%20would%20cost%20nothing%20for%20providers%20to%20go%20into%20business%20%E2%80%94%20the%20background%20checks%2C%20the%20trainings%2C%20the%20licensing%20would%20all%20be%20cost-free%2C%26quot%3B%20Furstenfeld%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20cost%20of%20parents%20would%20be%20heavily%20subsidized%20or%20publicly%20funded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BNobody%20would%20question%20not%20funding%20public%20schools.%20Why%20not%20childcare%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-daycare-cliff-crisis-landlords-zoning-regulations-federal-funding-expiring-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695723601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650c56df12dc4f001a178613%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-daycare-cliff-crisis-landlords-zoning-regulations-federal-funding-expiring-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20childcare%20providers%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20opening%20or%20expanding%20facilities%20because%20of%20zoning%20regulations%20and%20housing%20issues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-daycare-cliff-crisis-landlords-zoning-regulations-federal-funding-expiring-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22First%20appearance%20of%20celeb%20couples%20after%20marriage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695723600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103956839%2Cimgsize-60844.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3