aken%20after%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20defence%20ministry%20had%20cleared%20the%20visit.%20It%20was%20then%20forwarded%20to%20the%20foreign%20affairs%20ministry%2C%20from%20whom%20an%20official%20comment%20on%20the%20matter%20is%20still%20awaited.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20China%2C%20Shiyan%206%20(Experiment%206)%20is%20out%20on%20an%20%E2%80%9Cexpeditionary%20voyage%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20eastern%20part%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20after%20it%20had%20left%20Guangzhou%2C%20south%20China%E2%80%99s%20Guangdong%20Province.%20%E2%80%9COrganised%20by%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20Institute%20of%20Oceanology%20(SCSIO)%20under%20the%20Chinese%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%2C%20the%20vessel%20is%20scheduled%20to%20operate%20at%20sea%20for%2080%20days%20with%2028%20scientific%20research%20projects%20from%2013%20research%20teams%20onboard%2C%20covering%20a%20range%20of%20more%20than%2012%2C000%20nautical%20miles%20(roughly%2022%2C200%20km)%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20report%20from%20China%E2%80%99s%20state-run%20news%20channel%20CGTN%20had%20said%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChinese%20%E2%80%9Cresearch%20ships%E2%80%9D%20are%20said%20to%20usually%20have%20%E2%80%9Cdual%20purposes%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Flanka-clears-docking-of-chinese-research-ship-545633%5C%22%3Esays%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20while%20the%20primary%20aim%20is%20scientific%20exploration%2C%20what%20raises%20the%20hackles%20of%20other%20countries%20is%20the%20geopolitical%20purposes%20for%20which%20they%20are%20also%20deployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20said%20that%20the%20National%20Aquatic%20Resources%20Research%20and%20Development%20Agency%20(NARA)%20of%20Sri%20Lanka%20is%20a%20partner%20in%20the%20Chinese%20vessel%E2%80%99s%20research%20activities%20in%20Sri%20Lankan%20waters%2C%20and%20the%20research%20collected%20in%20the%20process%20would%20be%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20possession.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20concern%20over%20the%20visit%20of%20the%20Chinese%20vessel%20is%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20comes%20months%20after%20a%20Chinese%20warship%20was%20docked%20at%20the%20Colombo%20port%20for%20a%20few%20days.%20Earlier%2C%20another%20Chinese%20military%20ship%2C%20Yuan%20Wang%205%2C%20had%20visited%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20Hambantota%20port%20in%20August%20last%20year%20even%20after%20India%20as%20well%20as%20the%20US%20had%20expressed%20their%20concerns.%20China%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20had%20said%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Ccompletely%20unjustified%20for%20certain%20countries%20to%20cite%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98security%20concerns%E2%80%99%20to%20pressure%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20reassurances%2C%20India%20has%20conveyed%20to%20Colombo%20that%20it%20has%20misgivings%20about%20the%20visit%20of%20Chinese%20vessels%20to%20ports%20in%20Sri%20Lanka.%20However%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20underline%20to%20India%20that%20it%20will%20not%20allow%20its%20territory%20to%20be%20used%20for%20any%20activity%20that%20would%20threaten%20the%20security%20interests%20of%20India%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20recent%20meeting%20organised%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20high%20commission%20in%20Colombo%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20minister%20of%20ports%2C%20shipping%20and%20aviation%2C%20Nimal%20Siripala%20de%20Silva%2C%20had%20underlined%20the%20importance%20of%20%E2%80%9Cclose%20collaboration%2C%20exchange%20of%20knowledge%20and%20adaptation%20of%20new%20technology%20for%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20maritime%20sector%E2%80%9D.%20Silva%20had%20made%20the%20remarks%20at%20a%20curtain%20raiser%20organised%20by%20the%20Indian%20high%20commission%20in%20preparation%20for%20the%20Global%20Maritime%20India%20Summit%20to%20be%20held%20in%20Mumbai%20from%20October%2017%20to%2019.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695718471000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-con