rnment%20formalised%20counterterrorism%20as%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20primary%20task.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%20before%20it%20came%20to%20power%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20was%20clear%20that%20tasking%20the%20army%20to%20do%20only%20counter-terror%20operations%C2%A0%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20would%20meet%20two%20of%20its%20important%20objectives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFirst%2C%20it%20would%20cast%20Pakistan%20as%20a%20perpetual%20enemy%2C%20occupying%20both%20the%20army%20and%20the%20civilian%20population%E2%80%99s%20attention.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecond%2C%20by%20allowing%20Pakistan%20to%20function%20as%20shorthand%20for%20Muslim%2C%20the%20party%20would%20keep%20its%20core%20vote%20bank%20%E2%80%93%20Hindutva%20supporters%20%E2%80%93%20consolidated.%20This%20would%20help%20it%20in%20putting%20in%20motion%20its%20agenda%20of%20pushing%20for%20a%20Hindu%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Erashtra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Since%20the%20Army%20would%20be%20lauded%20for%20its%20successes%20against%20terrorists%2C%20catapulting%20it%20to%20the%20centre%20stage%20of%20national%20imagination%2C%20it%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20resist%20being%20used%20for%20the%20political%20objectives%20of%20the%20ruling%20party.%20Moreover%2C%20to%20garner%20the%20support%20of%20the%20veterans%2C%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98One%20Rank%2C%20One%20Pension%E2%80%99%20scheme%20was%20also%20announced.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%2013-lakh%20Army%E2%80%99s%20Order%20of%20Battle%20(ORBAT)%20or%20strength%20is%20around%20manpower%2C%20and%20nearly%2050%2C000%20soldiers%20join%20the%20rank%20of%20veterans%20each%20year%2C%20it%20was%20necessary%20to%20keep%20them%20aligned%20with%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98nationalist%E2%80%99%20thinking%20where%20perception%20(enhanced%20by%20a%20complicit%20media)%20would%20matter%20more%20than%20reality.%20The%20Air%20Force%20and%20Navy%2C%20whose%20ORBATs%20are%20around%20its%20combat%20platform%20would%2C%20with%20fewer%20manpower%2C%20follow%20the%20Army%E2%80%99s%20lead%20for%20personal%20glory%20and%20gratification.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fed7coxVUi1U%3Fsi%3DGg5nGiXqdRHHOPy-%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20the%20armed%20forces%20fall%20in%20line%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20this%20as%20the%20backdrop%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20quickly%20got%20to%20work%20on%20its%20agenda%20of%20aligning%20the%20Army%20(and%20military)%20to%20its%20political%20requirements.%20This%20was%20made%20possible%20in%20four%20successive%20steps.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%2C%20within%20weeks%20of%20coming%20to%20power%2C%20defence%20minister%20Arun%20Jaitley%20praised%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20CT%20ops%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20July%2022%2C%202014%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailypioneer.com%2F2014%2Findia%2Fgovt-will-not-allow-our-heads-to-bow-jaitley.html%5C%22%3Esuggested%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20fence%20on%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20(LC)%20be%20upgraded.%20Encouraged%20by%20this%2C%20the%20then-Nothern%20Army%20commander%20Lt%20General%20D.S.%20Hooda%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Findia-others%2Fcoming-a-new-winter-proof-loc-fence-with-sensors-and-night-vision-cameras%2F%5C%22%3Emedia%20in%20August%202015%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20fence%20would%20be%20strengthened%20by%20state-of-the-art%20sensors%20for%20surveillance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFencing%20of%20the%20active%20LC%20in%20July%202004%20by%20army%20chief%20General%20N.C.%20Vij%20was%20the%20Army%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20mistake.%20It%20instilled%20the%20Maginot%20mentality%20(defensive%20mindset)%20in%20the%20troops.%20Any%20worthwhile%20military%20commander%20the%20world%20over%20will%20attest%20that%20a%20fortification%20induces%20a%20false%20sense%20of%20security%20and%20stifles%20the%20attacking%20spirit%20of%20an%20army.%20Thus%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20fence%20gave%20assurance%20to%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20to%20continue%20with%20its%20peacetime%20training%20for%20war%20without%20worrying%20about%20Indian%20retaliation%20in%20the%20form%20of%20raids%20on%20their%20posts%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20a%20common%20activity%20by%20both%20sides%20in%20the%2090s.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20initiative%20passed%20completely%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20terrorists%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20their%20handlers%20across%20the%20military%20line.%20The%20latter%20dictated%20the%20rates%20of%20engagement%2C%20infiltration%2C%20areas%20to%20be%20activated%20and%20to%20what%20purpose%2C%20including%20methods%20of%20initiation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThroughout%20the%20nine-year%20tenure%20of%20defence%20minister%20A.K.%20Antony%20under%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government%2C%20there%20was%20a%20debate%20to%20dismantle%20the%20fence%20and%20progressively%20end%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20CT%20ops.%20Nothing%20came%20out%20of%20it%20since%20an%20indecisive%20Antony%20supported%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20viewpoint%20to%20continue%20with%20CT%20ops%20which%20gave%20it%20awards%2C%20honour%2C%20status%2C%20and%20perks%2C%20including%20total%20authority%20in%20the%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK.%20The%2015%20corps%20commander%20in%20Srinagar%20could%20ride%20roughshod%20over%20the%20elected%20state%20chief%20minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20Modi%20government%20formalising%20CT%20ops%20as%20the%20Army%E2%80%99s%20primary%20role%2C%20that%20Damocles%E2%80%99%20sword%20hanging%20over%20the%20Army%20leadership%E2%80%99s%20head%20was%20lifted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%2C%20addressing%20his%20first%20combined%20commander%E2%80%99s%20conference%20in%20Delhi%20in%20October%202014%2C%20Modi%20gave%20his%20threat%20assessment%20to%20the%20military%20leadership.%20In%20professional%20militaries%2C%20its%20leadership%20and%20not%20the%20prime%20minister%20determines%20the%20external%20threats%20facing%20the%20nation.%20But%20under%20the%20new%20political%20dispensation%20in%20India%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20told%20the%20military%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fprepare-for-a-changing-world-pm-narendra-modi-tells-armed-forces%2Farticleshow%2F44853126.cms%5C%22%3Ethat%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%98the%20threats%20may%20be%20known%2C%20but%20the%20enemy%20may%20be%20invisible.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20%E2%80%98threat%E2%80%99%20was%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98enemy%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20terrorists%2C%20who%20are%20faceless%2C%20nameless%2C%20and%20dispensable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Army%20gladly%20agreed%20to%20continue%20with%20CT%20ops%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Not%20to%20be%20left%20behind%2C%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20Arup%20Raha%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforceindia.net%2Ffirstperson%2Fthe-balance-sheet%2F%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%202016%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20must%20focus%20on%20deterring%20terrorist%20attacks%20or%20fighting%20the%20sub-conventional%20threats.%20We%20are%20training%20large%20number%20of%20personnel%20for%20this%20role.%20We%20are%20tweaking%20our%20tactics%20and%20are%20looking%20at%20equipment%20for%20this%20role.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20China%20factor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESadly%2C%20the%20armed%20forces%20were%20unmindful%20of%20what%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20was%20doing%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ealong%20the%20shared%20military%20line%20(Line%20of%20Actual%20Control)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eat%20that%20time.%20For%20example%2C%20in%202014%2C%20the%20PLA%20declared%20its%20new%20military%20strategy%20(which%20was%20as%20transformational%20as%20Mao%E2%80%99s%201956%20military%20strategy)%20with%20three%20peculiarities%3A%20maritime%20(naval)%20domain%20was%20mentioned%20for%20the%20first%20time%3B%20three%20new%20war%20domains%2C%20namely%20outer%20space%2C%20cyber%2C%20and%20electromagnetic%2C%20were%20added%20to%20the%20physical%20ones%20of%20land%2C%20sea%2C%20and%20air%3B%20and%20a%20new%20war%20concept%20of%20joint%20integrated%20operations%20called%20informatised%20war%20was%20announced.%20To%20consolidate%20informatised%20war%2C%20the%20PLA%20in%202015%20declared%20its%20biggest%20military%20reforms%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20five%20years%20%E2%80%93%20under%20which%20it%20created%20the%20Western%20Theatre%20Command%20(its%20largest%20land%20command)%20for%20war%20with%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInterestingly%2C%20alarmed%20by%20PLA%E2%80%99s%20rising%20capabilities%2C%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20in%202014%2C%20announced%20its%20third%20offset%20strategy%20underpinned%20by%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20and%20autonomy%20to%20offset%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20operational%20advantages.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F08233446%2FScreen-Shot-2020-09-08-at-11.34.34-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221127%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F08233446%2FScreen-Shot-2020-09-08-at-11.34.34-PM.png%201127w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F08233446%2FScreen-Shot-2020-09-08-at-11.34.34-PM-300x159.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F08233446%2FScreen-Shot-2020-09-08-at-11.34.34-PM-1024x542.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-478045%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22596%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20photograph%20released%20by%20PTI%20shows%20Peoples%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20soldiers%20reportedly%20near%20the%20Indian%20post%20near%20Mukhpari%20peak%20in%20Ladakh%20on%20September%207%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20made%20a%20purely%20military%20issue%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20cross-border%20terrorism%20into%20J%26amp%3BK%20into%20its%20political%20redline%20for%20improving%20relations%20with%20Pakistan.%20External%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20has%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20%E2%80%98it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20have%20a%20normal%20relationship%20with%20Pakistan%20until%20there%20is%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20policy%20of%20cross%20border%20terrorism.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECross-border%20terrorism%20is%20a%20common%20military%20strategy%20used%20to%20fight%20an%20enemy%20with%20larger%20numbers.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20has%20half%20the%20numbers%20as%20compared%20with%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%2013-lakh%20strength.%20In%20this%20strategy%2C%20without%20inducting%20its%20own%20soldiers%20in%20combat%2C%20the%20enemy%20uses%20terrorists%20to%20weaken%20the%20other%20side%E2%80%99s%20regular%20army%20by%20(a)%20unabated%20CT%20ops%2C%20and%20(b)%20keeping%20it%20away%20from%20its%20primary%20task%20of%20preparing%20for%20conventional%20war%20which%20requires%20regular%20training%20in%20Combined%20Arms%20Operations%20(CAO).%20That%20CT%20ops%20and%20CAO%20are%20as%20different%20as%20chalk%20and%20cheese%20has%20been%20proved%20twice%20before%20%E2%80%93%20during%20the%201999%20Operation%20Vijay%20(Kargil%20conflict)%3B%20and%20later%20during%20the%202001-2002%20Operation%20Parakram%20(after%20the%20attack%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20parliament).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20Kargil%20conflict%2C%20the%20commander%20of%20the%208th%20Mountain%20Division%20Maj0r%20General%20Mohinder%20Singh%20said%20that%20it%20took%20him%20weeks%20to%20reorient%20his%20troops%20doing%20CT%20ops%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efighting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20conflict.%20And%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eduring%20Operation%20Parakram%2C%20the%20northern%20army%20commander%20Lt%20General%20Rustom%20K.%20Nanavati%20had%20sought%20six%20months%E2%80%99%20time%20from%20the%20army%20chief%20General%20S.%20Padmanabhan%20to%20orient%20his%20forces%20from%20CT%20ops%20to%20conventional%20war%3B%20it%20was%20good%20that%20the%20Vajpayee%20government%20decided%20not%20to%20go%20to%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWays%20of%20ending%20cross-border%20terror%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20two%20ways%20of%20ending%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20cross-border%20terrorism.%20The%20first%20is%20for%20India%20to%20start%20meaningful%20talks%20with%20Pakistan%3B%20once%20this%20happens%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20will%20control%20the%20terrorist%20flow%20into%20Kashmir.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpenguin.co.in%2Fbook%2Fneither-a-hawk-nor-a-dove%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Khurshid%20Mahmud%20Kasuri%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20from%202002%20to%202007%20under%20the%20Musharraf%20regime%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%202005%20and%202006%2C%20I%20started%20hearing%20in%20hushed%20tones%20at%20the%20Presidency%20and%20in%20some%20other%20high-level%20meetings%20that%20centres%20had%20been%20set%20up%20to%20wean%20away%20militants%20from%20their%20past%20and%20impart%20skills%20to%20them%20which%20would%20help%20them%20integrate%20better%20in%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20this%20period%2C%20backchannel%20peace%20talks%20were%20happening%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20which%20eventually%20led%20to%20Musharraf%E2%80%99s%20four-point%20formula%20for%20peace%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20other%20way%20is%20for%20the%20Indian%20military%20to%20build%20credible%20deterrence%20(warfighting%20capability)%20which%20would%20force%20Pakistan%20to%20review%20its%20misadventure%20lest%20it%20boomerangs.%20In%2033%20years%2C%20since%201990%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20leadership%20has%20preferred%20to%20get%20its%20soldiers%20killed%20in%20CT%20ops%20rather%20than%20prepare%20itself%20credibly%20to%20defeat%20the%20Pakistan%20Army.%20This%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20suits%20both%20the%20Army%20leadership%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%20which%20has%20demanded%20that%20Pakistan%20cease%20cross-border%20terrorism%2C%20while%20adding%20that%20the%20only%20issue%20to%20discuss%20bilaterally%20is%20the%20return%20of%20Pakistan%20Occupied%20Kashmir%20and%20Gilgit-Baltistan%20to%20India.%20It%20suits%20India%20not%20to%20have%20normal%20ties%20with%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20four%2C%20the%20government%20deftly%20co-opted%20the%20mainstream%20media%20to%20carry%20forth%20its%20political%20agenda%20to%20the%20masses%20through%20the%20relentless%20broadcasting%20of%20the%20party-approved%20narrative.%20This%20has%20been%20made%20possible%20through%20the%20triple%20combination%20of%20allurement%2C%20punishment%20and%20ideological%20convergence.%20By%20conflating%20nationalism%20with%20patriotism%20and%20criticism%20of%20the%20government%20with%20anti-national%20activities%2C%20the%20government%20facilitated%20the%20collaboration%20of%20the%20retired%20military%20officers%20and%20the%20media%20for%20this%20purpose.%20After%20all%2C%20who%20could%20be%20a%20bigger%20nationalist%20than%20the%20military%20which%20sacrifices%20itself%20for%20the%20nation%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20consequence%20of%20this%20was%20that%20any%20criticism%20of%20the%20government%20policy%20was%20countered%20by%20the%20argument%20of%20a%20soldier%E2%80%99s%20sacrifice%20for%20the%20nation%2C%20thereby%20communicating%20to%20the%20public%20through%20the%20media%20that%20a%20true%20patriot%20is%20the%20person%20who%20willingly%20sacrifices%20his%20life%20for%20the%20government%20without%20asking%20questions.%20In%20the%20last%20nine%20years%2C%20many%20Indians%2C%20who%20still%20regard%20the%20mainstream%20media%20as%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20both%20news%20and%20knowledge%2C%20have%20internalised%20the%20narrative%20that%20questioning%20the%20government%20is%20an%20anti-national%20activity.%20And%20since%20the%20military%20does%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20bidding%20unquestionably%2C%20asking%20questions%20of%20the%20military%20is%20not%20just%20seditious%20but%20sacrilegious%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20media-military%20nexus%20portrays%20Pakistan%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20primary%20threat.%20Then%20through%20sly%20manipulation%20of%20this%20narrative%2C%20in%20which%20religion%20is%20diabolically%20introduced%2C%20Indian%20Muslims%20are%20presented%20as%20an%20internal%20security%20concern%2C%20which%20all%20nationalist%20citizens%20must%20watch%20out%20for.%20This%20is%20not%20only%20the%20politicisation%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%2C%20but%20the%20communalisation%20of%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20apolitical%20and%20a-religious%20institutions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F03205026%2F2020_7img03_Jul_2020_PTI03-07-2020_000222B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F03